<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNCILMAN LINDSAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is a tribute to Gil Lindsay. 
</P>
<P>
When various humane organizations in 1969 urged the Los Angeles City Council to 
establish a public spay and neuter clinic, Gil Lindsay was the outstanding city 
councilman who led us to victory. 
</P>
<P>
As a result, we now have three spay and neuter clinics in Los Angeles, together 
with four in the county. Millions of dollars have been saved by the public and 
countless animals lives which would be destroyed by our city and county 
shelters at considerable public expense have been prevented. 
</P>
<P>
We are saddened by Councilman Lindsay's condition and fervently hope for his 
recovery. 
</P>
<P>
EDWARD NEWMAN, Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Councilman Gilbert Lindsay in 1988. Los Angeles Times 
