torch at the shady site of a Tarzana statuary company. Bunny Delluge, who runs 
the firm, said "We want to keep this place just the way it is," though curbs on 
growth would lower the land's value. RICHARD DERK / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
