<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 41 MEN ARRESTED IN PROSTITUTION SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police arrested 41 men on prostitution-related charges this weekend in an 
undercover operation in which female police officers posed as prostitutes in 
Pacoima, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The men, ranging in age from 18 to 50, were arrested on suspicion of soliciting 
the women for acts of prostitution. The men received misdemeanor citations and 
were released, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the crackdown, which ran from 5:30 p.m. Saturday until 12:30 a.m. 
Sunday, is part of a continuing effort to keep the area around Kelowna Street 
and San Fernando Road free of prostitutes. Residents in the area complain that 
the prostitutes attract undesirable people into their neighborhoods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
