<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121090-0040 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 320153 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 10, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 2; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
77 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: WINTER SPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Germany's Gunda Kleeman set a world record in the women's 3,000 meters in a 
World Cup speedskating meet at Calgary, breaking the mark set by her long-time 
idol, Yvonne Van Gennip of the Netherlands. Kleeman's time of 4:10.80 was more 
than a second better than the mark of 4:11.94 set by Van Gennip, a triple gold 
medalist at the 1988 Calgary Winter Olympics. Van Gennip finished third in 
4:21.06, well behind second-place Heike Warnicke, also of Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
