<DOCID> 320181 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 10, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 22; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
146 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; 
</P>
<P>
ED BURKE MEMORIAL FUTURITY IS 5TH VICTORY FOR JACKS DASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jacks Dash won the $334,000 Ed Burke Memorial Futurity by three-quarters of a 
length over Reeds Signature Saturday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Henry Garcia, Jacks Dash ran the 350-yard course in 17.55 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Tolls Touch finished third, a nose behind Reeds Signature. 
</P>
<P>
The winner paid $6.60, $4.80 and $3.60. Reeds Signature, a 40-1 shot, returned 
$21.40 and $9.20 and Tolls Touch paid $3.40. Each horse in the field of 10 
2-year-olds carried 122 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Vital Sign, the 2-1 favorite, crossed under the wire fourth, but was 
disqualified and placed last for interference when he lugged out from the rail 
post and impeded A One Man Band. 
</P>
<P>
Jacks Dash, a gelded son of Dash for Cash, earned $150,300 for his fifth 
victory in 11 starts and increased his total winnings to $171,503. 
</P>
<P>
Jacks Dash also won the Breeders Freshman Classic at Los Alamitos on Nov. 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
