<TEXT>
<P>
More State Trucking Firms Failing: The number of trucking company failures in 
California rose 11% the first three quarters of 1990, reversing a four-year 
downward trend, according to Dunn &amp; Bradstreet. 
</P>
<P>
About 130 carriers failed the first nine months, up from 117 last year. If the 
trend continues, there will be 175 failures this year, more than in any year 
since 1986, according to the California Trucking Assn. Last year there were 157 
failures. Carriers operating in the Los Angeles basin, where environmental 
regulation is strictest, are among the most vulnerable to failure, the 
association said. 
</P>
