</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pop music star Paula Abdul suffered minor injuries Sunday when her black Jaguar 
rear-ended another car on Laurel Canyon Boulevard in Studio City, triggering a 
three-car accident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old singer was taken by ambulance to AMI Medical Center of North 
Hollywood with complaints of neck and back pain after the 12:45 p.m. collision, 
Los Angeles Police Sgt. Christopher Vasquez said. 
</P>
<P>
The Grammy Award winner singer was treated and released, a hospital spokeswoman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Abdul was driving north on Laurel Canyon when she collided with a car driven by 
Charles Koko, 37, of North Hollywood. 
