</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard man who was shot in the abdomen in a drive-by attack drove himself to 
the hospital for medical treatment, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Luis Ruiz, 34, was standing near his home in the 4400 block of Cypress 
Road about 5 p.m. Saturday when a compact car drove up to him and a gunman 
fired several shots, said Sgt. Fred Berry of the Oxnard Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Police had no further information about the shooting, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Ruiz drove himself to Ventura County Medical Center, where he was hospitalized. 
He was reported in serious but stable condition Sunday after undergoing 
surgery, a nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
Berry said police are looking for the driver of small gray or brown Honda who 
may have been responsible for the shooting. PSYCHE PASCUAL 
