<P>
PLAN AHEAD: Speaking of arts grants (above), Security Pacific Bank paid $25,000 
this year to be honorary producer of South Coast Rep's "A Christmas Carol," but 
when the programs came out, oops, the usual credit was missing. . . . Smoothing 
this over fell to SCR receptionist Holly Van Holt and her volunteers, who are 
applying 10,000 gold stickers to programs to credit the bank. "I'm only on the 
thousandth sticker," she said. "I'm not even close." 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
