<TEXT>
<P>
Bonuses were paid today to Japan's 4.46 million government workers, which 
include employees at government-owned corporations. 
</P>
<P>
Officials said the bonuses totaled about $24.3 billion, which is equivalent to 
2 1/2 months' pay averaging about $5,450 per person. 
</P>
<P>
The officials said public workers will receive an additional amount of year-end 
bonuses by the end of this year, as Parliament is expected to approve a wage 
hike bill for public-sector workers at its session convened today. 
</P>
<P>
Most Japanese workers receive bonuses twice a year -- summer and year-end. 
</P>
